text:
4419 Kings Highway, west side, 50 yards north of Troy Avenue, showing the John A. Voorhis House. The center part of the house was built in 1800; the right section in 1853; and the left wing after 1853. John A. Voorhis was assemblyman from Kings County and supervisor of the town of Flatlands.

View 1: 1922
Views 2,3: 1925
View 4: 1928

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

text:
Troy Ave., near King's Highway and westward towards the Flatlands Dutch Reformed Church, whose spire may be seen beyond the trees. Once, a brook, known as Van Mater's Skating Pond ran easterly through the Willow trees seen in the foreground.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
